VPD_NOMINALSYNOPSIS: Billy, 98, who suffers from dementia, was involved in an incident when he wandered onto the highway, causing significant safety concerns. Despite his history as a repeated victim and perpetrator, no consent was given to share this information publicly. After being escorted home by Bradley Howell, a colleague, Billy inadvertently entered his neighbor’s house, escalating concerns about his repeated vulnerability due to cognitive decline. This situation underscores the need for closer monitoring and support for Billy.
VPD_WELLBEINGCOMMENTS: Billy demonstrates signs of dementia and has experienced repeated victimization.
